---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ear Training for Swaras | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Develop your musical ear to identify swaras by sound — essential for raga mastery. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Ear Training for Swaras</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-practice capitalize">practice</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 25 min · Practice Module</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Ear Training for Swaras</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Develop your musical ear to identify swaras by sound — essential for raga mastery.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Ear training and hand training must develop together</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Start by deeply recognizing Sa — your anchor note</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Then learn Pa — the perfect fifth always consonant with Sa</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Work outward from Sa and Pa to other swaras</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>10 minutes of daily listening practice develops pitch recognition</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>Why Ear Training Matters</h2>
      <p>A harmonium player with strong ears can hear a raga and immediately begin playing it identify wrong notes in their own playing tune their instrument by ear and improvise freely within ragas. Ear training is not a separate subject from harmonium technique — it is the inner foundation that makes all external technique musically meaningful and expressive.</p>

      <h2>Exercise 1 Sa Recognition</h2>
      <p>Play a note on the harmonium. Without looking at the keyboard decide if it sounds like Sa or not Sa. If it is Sa notice how it sounds — stable grounded complete settled. If it is not Sa notice the tension or incompleteness. Play Sa (A key) listen for 10 seconds then play random notes and decide: is this Sa? Repeat daily for 3 minutes. This builds your aural anchor.</p>

      <h2>Exercise 2 The Sa Pa Interval</h2>
      <p>The Sa-Pa interval (perfect fifth) is the most consonant interval in Indian music — almost like two versions of the same note. Play Sa then Pa and listen to their natural blend. Now play Sa and other notes and try to identify which is Pa purely by its consonant quality. This interval recognition is the foundation of all further ear development.</p>

      <h2>Exercise 3 Swara Naming</h2>
      <p>Play any note on the harmonium and try to name it before looking. Start with just the 7 natural swaras staying in Madhya octave. Over weeks your swara recognition will steadily improve. Advanced students can identify all 12 notes correctly from a single hearing — this is called Sargam Siddhi. Begin this practice now even if results seem slow at first.</p>

      <h2>Daily Ear Training Routine</h2>
      <p>Spend 10 minutes daily: 3 minutes play Sa and then stop playing but try to continue hearing it in your inner ear — developing inner hearing. 3 minutes play two-note intervals and name them. 4 minutes listen to any recording of Indian classical music and try to follow along noting when you recognize a familiar swara phrase or interval. This daily listening practice is the fastest path to musical ear development.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>